author = {Kuldeep Singh Kaswan and Jagjit Singh Dhatterwal and Suman Chahar},
keywords = {Surgical robots, kinematics, robotic manipulators, Lagrangian mechanics, path planning algorithms, robotics, surgical procedure, manufacturing engineering, control systems, mechanical systems, computer-aided engineering, computational intelligence, neurosurgery},
abstract = {Surgical robots are one of the biggest medical shifts in the contemporary world, providing precision, dexterity levels, and minimally invasive surgery. Thus, the description of the kinematics as well as the dynamics of these robots would enhance the understanding of the robots in achieving safe and accurate operations within the surgical procedures. In this chapter, a comprehensible review and analysis of the principles of kinematic and dynamic models in surgical robots have been undertaken alongside the display of their importance, difficulty, and expectation in the feature. Surgical robots—like the Da Vinci surgical system—are increasingly being used in one surgical specialty or another because of their variable benefits in that they can improve the precision of surgical operations. Nevertheless, to ensure their efficiency, their kinematics and dynamics must be modeled correctly. This chapter provides an overview of kinematics and dynamics concepts to be used in advanced surgical robot designs. It encompasses as far as forward and inverse kinematics, movement dynamics, and control methodologies. Examples have been used from the real world to support the learning objectives of these concepts. The enhanced functionality of surgeries means that such procedures require profound control of the robotic manipulators to perform their functions; therefore, specific knowledge about their kinematic designs and dynamic patterns is essential. Some of the issues like the size of the workspace, the constraints between the links, and the timing requirements are rather daunting to deal with when it comes to achieving high performance. The primary goal of this chapter is therefore to review the principles of kinematics and dynamics in surgical robotics and present the readers with the background knowledge as well as pointers regarding their application. It looks at areas of concern and control methods to stimulate the furthering of innovation and development. An important understanding of these kinematic and dynamic models is presented in this chapter, which unveils the dynamics of interaction between a robotic manipulator and a surgical workspace. Furthermore, it surfaces the tools of impedance control and haptic feedback that hold prominence in making surgical apparitions and augment the surgeon’s ability. In summary, this reflection highlights the need for practical-oriented application of surgical robots where theory is integrated with base practical approaches to improve the effectiveness of current healthcare systems.}
}
